Minh Huynh is a PhD student in the http://www.cs.ucdavis.edu Computer Science Department at UC Davis, where he earned a BS degree in computer science in 2002. Currently, his research is on Metro Ethernet Network under the guidance of professor http://www.cs.ucdavis.edu/~prasant Prasant Mohapatra. His focus is on resilience, network load balancing, QoS, and security. His homepage is here http://wwwcsif.cs.ucdavis.edu/~huynh.
He is also interested in Judo where he is a member of the Davis Judo Team UC Davis Judo Team.
